argument-reference:
Argument Reference

This resource supports the following arguments:

  • name - (Required) The name of the container. Must contain alphanumeric characters or underscores.
  • tags - (Optional) A map of tags to assign to the resource. If configured with a provider default_tags configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.
attribute-reference:
Attribute Reference

This resource exports the following attributes in addition to the arguments above:

  • arn - The ARN of the container.
  • endpoint - The DNS endpoint of the container.
  • tags_all - A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider default_tags configuration block.
import:
Import

In Terraform v1.5.0 and later, use an import block to import MediaStore Container using the MediaStore Container Name. For example:

terraformimport { to = aws_media_store_container.example id = "example"}

Using terraform import, import MediaStore Container using the MediaStore Container Name. For example:

console% terraform import aws_media_store_container.example example
